I keep getting the following error message "cursor timed out (timeout:
30000, time left: 0:0, status: 0)" no matter what timeout i set for
the cursor. So i made a test script .

Basically I think $cursor->timeout() does not have any effects at all. I'm marking this as Major since this really affects long background processing tasks


The pastebin is here http://pastebin.com/4gaZRPdy

<?php
    $mongo = new Mongo('localhost');
    $db = $mongo->selectDB("foo");
    echo MongoCursor::$timeout; //prints out 30000
    echo '--';
    $db->users->insert(array('name' => 'user1', 'pass' => '123'));
    $db->users->insert(array('name' => 'user2', 'pass' => '123'));
    $db->users->insert(array('name' => 'user3', 'pass' => '123'));
    $cursor = $db->users->find();
    $cursor->getNext();
    $cursor->timeout(50000); // $cursor->timeout(-1); has same effect

    echo MongoCursor::$timeout; //still prints out 30000. WTF?

    sleep(40);
    var_dump($cursor->getNext());
    sleep(60);// sleep 60 to get passed 50 seconds
    var_dump($cursor->getNext()); //Should raise MongoCursor timeout
exception. It doesn't. WTF

    die();

